raw_mentions: The compound obtained was subjected to the IM-9 binding assay, the [Sar<sup>9</sup>, Met(O<sub>2</sub>)<sup>11</sup>]substance P-induced tapping test and the verapamil binding study as described before, with the results of less than 0.1 nM, 52% (% inhibition at 0.3 mg/kg scoring) and more than 3000 nM, respectively.
